    <summary>Beautiful command-line tool for Letterboxd with interactive TUI and rich terminal display</summary>
    <description>
lbxd is a powerful command-line tool written in Rust that brings Letterboxd to your terminal. View any user's movie activity, ratings, and reviews in beautiful ASCII art and stylized text.

## Features
- 🎭 Interactive TUI for browsing complete movie collections
- 📽️ View recent activity, ratings, and reviews for any user
- 🔍 Search functionality for titles in user activity
- 🎬 Movie database integration with TMDB
- 📤 Export data to JSON or Markdown formats
- 🎨 Beautiful terminal display with ASCII art and posters
- ⚙️ Configurable settings and user preferences  
- 💾 Intelligent caching for offline access
- 🌍 Cross-platform support (Windows, macOS, Linux)

## Quick Start
After installation, try:
- `lbxd recent username` - View recent activity
- `lbxd movie "Inception"` - Search for movies
- `lbxd browse username` - Interactive TUI mode
- `lbxd --help` - See all commands

## Requirements
- Python 3.x (auto-installed if missing)
- Optional: viu for enhanced image display

No API keys required - works out of the box!
